<item>
            <title>[KAFKA-8806] Kafka.poll spends significant amount of time in KafkaConsumer.updateAssignmentMetadataIfNeeded</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-8806</link>
                <project id="12311720" key="KAFKA">Kafka</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Comparing the performance profile of 2.2.0 and 2.3.0, we are seeing significant performance differences in the &lt;tt&gt;KafkaConumer.updateAssignmentMetadataIfNeeded()&lt;/tt&gt; method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The call to &lt;tt&gt;KafkaConsumer.updateAssignmentMetadataIfNeeded()&lt;/tt&gt; now represents roughly 25% of CPU time spent in &lt;tt&gt;KafkaConsumer.poll()&lt;/tt&gt;, when before it only represented less than 5%.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most of the extra time appears to be spent in &lt;tt&gt;KafkaConsumer.validateOffsetsIfNeeded()&lt;/tt&gt;, which did not show up in previous profiles.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
